poroporoaki
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:(in Maori oratory) a panegyric or farewell, often to a deceased person; a funeral lament.
Origin:Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: also poroaki; also as verb
